## Greptile Summary

This PR addresses a potential integer overflow issue in the `ApplyTextEdits` method within the Unity MCP Bridge's script management system. The change modifies how UTF-8 byte counts are tracked during text editing operations by switching from a 32-bit `int` to a 64-bit `long` for the `totalBytes` variable and adding overflow protection with a `checked` block.

The modification is part of the `ManageScript.cs` file, which handles script editing operations in Unity's MCP Bridge. This bridge enables communication between Unity applications and Large Language Models via the Model Context Protocol. The `ApplyTextEdits` method processes text modifications and validates their size, making it critical for the system's text editing functionality.

The change integrates seamlessly with the existing codebase architecture. The method continues to function identically from an external perspective, but now handles edge cases more robustly. The `long` type provides a practically unlimited range for byte counting (9.2 √ó 10^18 vs 2.1 √ó 10^9 for `int`), while the `checked` block ensures any theoretical overflow would throw an `OverflowException` rather than silently wrapping to negative values.

## Important Files Changed

<details>
<summary>File Changes</summary>

| Filename | Score | Overview |
|----------|-------|----------|
| `UnityMcpBridge/Editor/Tools/ManageScript.cs` | 5/5 | Changed `totalBytes` from `int` to `long` and added overflow protection with `checked` block |

</details>
